latestPosts.caption:
You know how everyone’s hair stops growing at a certain length and that’s where your hair will sit? (Especially with curly hair)…

Well the length where my hair naturally likes to sit is LONG, and I truly do factor this into my hair texture. My really defined hair that I’ve had is starting to become less defined all because my hair is growing past chest length, and I’m excited to welcome back my old hair texture! 

But guys have to promise me, no comments about how my hair is becoming “unhealthy”… 😂 I fear my long undefined hair is my actual texture. Too many people assume that when my hair is long it’s unhealthy because it’s undefined, but curl definition shouldn’t be the main indicator of curl health! 

Where does your hair stop growing?
